flowRoot.flowPara: Distances are measured as average OF (= 'OpticalFlow') pixel displacement vector lengths.
For performance reasons, we only calculate the OF vector once for each frame f as f - kA (i.e. origin = kA),
the distance from f to the other keyframe kB can then be calculated because the vector kB - kA was saved previously.
Current frame is saved as keyframe kA
Distance between new frame and kA is smaller than min_disp_triangl, forget all data of the current frame
Distance between new frame and kA is now >= min_disp_triangl; from now on, do pose estimation and triangulation between new frame and kA
Distance between new frame and kA is now >= min_disp_keyfrm; new frame is saved as keyframe kB
keyfrm_ratio = a / (a+b) >= min_keyfrm_ratio, so we don't need to touch the keyframes, nothing special
keyfrm_ratio = a / (a+b) < min_keyfrm_ratio, so we swap the keyframes, thus pose estimation and triangulation are now based on the new kA (= old kB)
keyfrm_ratio = a / (a+b) >= min_keyfrm_ratio, so we don't need to touch the keyframes, nothing special
Distances from new frame to both keyframes kA and kB are >= min_disp_keyfrm; kB becomes kA, and new frame is saved as keyframe kB, thus pose estimation and triangulation are now based on the new kA
keyfrm_ratio = a / (a+b) >= min_keyfrm_ratio, so we don't need to touch the keyframes, nothing special
minimal OF displacement to do a reliable calculation of the fundamental matrix
minimal OF displacement between two consequetive keyframes;
Bounds: 2*min_disp_triangl < min_disp_keyfrm < half of the maximal allowed OF displacement
where: a = distance between keyframe kA and frame
b = distance between frame and keyframe kB
